# Kanin-loop (CodeRabbit review convergence)

When you are getting a `task/*` branch review-ready before a PR, run the
**kanin-loop** instead of hand-prompting fixes:

1. In **Cursor**, run **`/rabbit-loop`**, **or** open and follow
   **`docs/skills/rabbit-loop.md`** (same workflow in any editor).
   If the pass tracks a GitHub issue, apply the suggested `#N · short topic`
   title via `docs/skills/session-title-adapters.md` (Cursor: MCP `rename_chat`).
2. **Workflow preflight** (step 0b): `scripts/rabbit_workflow_context.sh` → review
   `.rabbit-loop/preflight.html` (plain git vs GitButler, local `task/*` lanes, open PRs).
   Ack: `--ack` or `rabbit_loop.sh --ack-workflow`. Rationale: GitHub #240 — do not rely on
   `git ls-remote` alone when other agents may have local But lanes.
3. Loop: `scripts/rabbit_loop.sh` (workflow gate + CodeRabbit `--agent` + `scripts/run_autotests.sh`)
   → fix **only within** `docs/decisions/agent-review-contract.md` → repeat until
   `RABBIT_LOOP: CONVERGED`. Cap at 3 iterations; escalate Critical / out-of-scope.
4. Ship gate (judgment, not file type): push + open the PR, then
   `scripts/rabbit_loop.sh --classify-merge`. `SAFE` → **auto-merge** when CONVERGED.
   `NEEDS_HUMAN` (report/invoice engine, `collectors/`, `outputs/`, deps, CI,
   governance) → generate a checklist with `scripts/rabbit_loop.sh --manual-test-plan`
   (real command + judgeable expected outcome per step), post it, and pause.

Base defaults to `origin/main` — keep it fresh. Canonical workflow:
**`docs/skills/rabbit-loop.md`**. Policy: **`AGENTS.md`**.
